{"type":"message","id":"4ddda111","parentId":"eb0473e0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:18:04.322Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The page keeps timing out waiting for `.price` even though it says \"24 locators resolved\". The issue seems to be that the price elements exist but the script can't properly read them. Let me try a different approach - just wait for networkidle and get the text content.\n\nActually, looking at the original ctrip_tracker.py script, it also had the same issue with `tyo` route. The issue is that the `.price` selector resolves to elements but they're not \"visible\" according to Playwright's definition. The error says \"waiting for locator('.price') to be visible\" but then \"Proceeding with the first one\" - so there are 24 elements but they're not considered visible.\n \nLet me try switching to `state=\"attached\"` instead, which just waits for the elements to be in the DOM without requiring visibility. The existing code already catches the timeout and continues anyway, so even if it fails it should still grab the text. I could also try waiting for `networkidle` or just giving it more time to load."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vcrx06l5ekkg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python C:\\ADHD_agent\\openclaw\\workspace\\check_direct.py 2>&1","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774361875617}}
